What you need to know:  On Monday, Nandi Hills Level Four Hospital said the student had died of severe pneumonia, septicaemia (sepsis or serious bloodstream infection), and acute peptic ulcersHospital Superintendent Elikan Chirchir dismissed the assault reportsHowever, Kiptanui's mother said her son was in perfect health when he left home a week agoKiptanui’s family and the local community say the report by Dr Chirchir raises questions because a post-mortem to establish the cause of the death has not even been done